author: Curt Mills
title: New Bush ad ridicules Trump's readiness
text:
A new ad out from Jeb Bush lambasts Donald Trump's readiness to be commander-in-chief. The ad is titled "Judgment."
The ad starts out with a serious tone, but then shifts to lighter fare in order to make its point. The almost two-minute spot, replete with goofy music, splices together humorous pictures and videos of Trump, juxtaposed against criticisms of Trump from media personalities.
Related Story: http://www.washingtonexaminer.com/article/2574118/ Bush's teases of the video on Twitter included "our national security isn't a reality TV show" and ".@RealDonaldTrump's absurd comments again raise questions on whether he possesses the judgment to be President."
  Jeb still livid about Trump 9/11 comments "He kept us safe and united the country. There's no denying that," Bush said.
